
    THOUSANDS of people posted their favourite photos of Robbie Malinga on social media. On top of having a talent for music, Malinga was also a people’s person, as can be seen in the many messages his fans posted after news of his death broke. Following Malinga’s tragic death on Christmas Day, here are some Facebook posts: -  Samkelo Dlulane wrote: “What a sad day for Mzansi. RIP, Bra Robbie. We will miss your funny jokes.” -  Nomtha Tshawekazi: “Rest in peace, Robbie. I remember grabbing and hugging you on 18 March 2014. You were laughing and I’ll always remember the fat hug you gave me.” -  Shakes Motsetse: “We have lost a kwaito pioneer who paved the way for future generations of artists. We send our deepest sympathies to his loved ones.” -  Nyamankulu Esethu: “I’m saddened by the death of Malinga. For some reason, I was playing his videos the night before he died.” -  Felo Le Tee: “I wish I could have met you, listened to you, and worked with you. I wish I grew up in your presence to know and understand more.”if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstPdFbk4ibS_7zO-uInNdJj1Kk7LD9RNSz1SWdL-maEy-AZsaLXwyDO91ZquXQOlJpHQYc5o5vEULbLSHf92Pt2Tuxlki7ti8BhX51Ls6rHwVl5n5wV6Ksxc6xkPAWwdK_1Kcq_IaFQ9L-T7kCgWoRo_lwpEYDzJvU2QRoq-2-2QuaHWjca3Pa56MeE7gVEbmTuhMdEaEmFZe6VE9VxDF4CWHfdfVV5-xDPZR1WOSTXeQjy4I-aYoLCutszwT5cDwIzabr2PSsuXc8q__98blPccjJUQQ8\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzKe2T1zQOGf_EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
